            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div id="body">
<article id="article">
<header><section>
<p>Consistency is key with those spines...</p>
</section></header><div><section>
<figure><a title="&quot;Get Your Act Together&quot; - Fans Aren't Happy With Clear River Games' Toaplan Collections 1" href="https://images.nintendolife.com/de0c312c3be2a/get-your-act-together-fans-arent-happy-with-clear-river-games-toaplan-collections-1.large.jpg"></a><figcaption><em>Image: Toaplan / Tatsujin</em></figcaption></figure><p>Toaplan rights holder Tatsujin has been busy over the past couple of years leveraging the company's enviable selection of arcades hits, with a wide range of collections appearing across multiple devices, including <a href="https://www.nintendolife.com/games/nintendo-switch/toaplan_arcade_garage_zero_fire">Switch</a>, <a href="https://www.timeextension.com/games/evercade/toaplan_arcade_1">Evercade</a> and <a href="https://www.timeextension.com/news/2024/03/toaplans-truxton-ii-grind-stormer-twin-hawk-and-dogyuun-are-coming-to-steam"><strong>Steam</strong></a>.</p>
<p>The latest effort is a two-pronged approach, with <a href="https://www.nintendolife.com/games/switch-eshop/toaplan_arcade_collection_vol_1">Toaplan Arcade Collection Vol 1</a> and <a href="https://www.nintendolife.com/games/switch-eshop/toaplan_arcade_collection_vol_2">Toaplan Arcade Collection Vol 2</a> coming to Switch in digital and physical forms.</p>
<p>Publisher Clear River Games is responsible for the latter, and has attracted some criticism when it comes to quality control.</p><div><figure data-videoid="C1rrCdi_XjA" data-start="0" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/C1rrCdi_XjA?rel=0&amp;hd=1&amp;showinfo=0&amp;modestbranding=0&amp;autohide=1"><iframe title="YouTube Video" src="javascript:''" data-src-fallback="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/C1rrCdi_XjA?rel=0&amp;hd=1&amp;showinfo=0&amp;modestbranding=0&amp;autohide=1" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/C1rrCdi_XjA?rel=0&amp;hd=1&amp;showinfo=0&amp;modestbranding=0&amp;autohide=1" data-consent="targeting" type="text/html" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" width="890" height="501" data-src-primis="https://live.primis.tech/live/liveView.php?s=117114&amp;vp_content=embed3be067gslqxi&amp;schain=1.0,1!ziffdavis.com,22392450815,1"></iframe><figcaption><p><a title="Watch This Video on YouTube" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C1rrCdi_XjA" rel="noopener">Watch on <strong><span></span> YouTube</strong> <span></span></a></p>
<p>Subscribe to <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/nintendolife?sub_confirmation=1">Nintendo Life</a> on <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/nintendolife?sub_confirmation=1"><span>YouTube</span><span>830k</span></a></p>
</figcaption></figure></div>
<figure><a title="&quot;Get Your Act Together&quot; - Fans Aren't Happy With Clear River Games' Toaplan Collections 1" href="https://images.nintendolife.com/4dbf85ddfab83/get-your-act-together-fans-arent-happy-with-clear-river-games-toaplan-collections-1.large.jpg"></a><figcaption><em>Image: <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/billycupid.bsky.social/post/3lwgzrytslc2d">@billycupid.bsky.social</a></em></figcaption></figure>
<p>As spotted by <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/billycupid.bsky.social/post/3lwgzrytslc2d">billycupid</a> on Bluesky, there's no Switch logo on the spine of the first volume, while the second lacks a full-stop after 'Vol' – something which <em>is</em> present on Vol 1.</p>
<p>"Come on guys, get your act together," says the social media poster. "People are going to start thinking you’ve just shat out a couple of half-baked collections on the cheap."</p>
<p>Clear River isn't alone when it comes to this kind of mistake – it can happen to the best of us, as Capcom found out with both <a href="https://www.nintendolife.com/games/wii/okami">Okami</a> (which had the IGN logo on its cover) and <a href="https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2012/01/north_american_resident_evil_packaging_is_wrong">Resident Evil Revelations</a> (which got the spelling of the game's name wrong).</p>
